    sep.mvc
    Abstract classes for the basic model-view-controller (MVC) architecture you will use in this exercise.
  • Classes in sep.mvc used by sep.mvc 
    Class and Description
    AbstractController
    A Controller is used to assemble the Model and view(s), and is responsible for coordinating operations between them to form the application as a whole.
    AbstractModel
    The Model is the most fundamental component in an MVC application - it encapsulates the application's core data structures.
    AbstractView
    A View provides the front-end user interface, which includes appropriate presentation of the relevant model data to the user.
